<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-9099B721-8AEB-4207-BB91-46B5A93F6CAE" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-9099B721-8AEB-4207-BB91-46B5A93F6CAE" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">01 How to replace the Micro SD card of the UV <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Lamp control PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 01PBA03 </compcodenr></comp></title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Dis-assembly</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-F8EE43B1-36AF-4F86-8810-3B686A03AF19" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li id="LI_53184B16D403439F881DA2AB90C20E0F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Go to COLD SDS and disconnect the Service jumper. 
</p></li><li id="LI_5176772B6144483082244285366FC178" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the top cover. 
</p><note type="important" id="GUID-7215619B-4D8E-42B1-B219-10C1EF6B5FB5" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not lean on the strip support. 
</p></note></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Do 
<xref keyref="01DISA009" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-86992A46-53DB-4CBA-A0E9-09BE333CCEFA.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>01 How to remove the Lamp control PBA ( 01PBA03 ;)</xref> 
</p></li></ol></prereq><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_BF7CE9B36BC446D897CD6D84C8FE9EBA" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_AC9058106BF3408FB35C50B0C64D3001" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Micro SD card with the following specifications: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Micro SD card. Greater than 2 GB. Less than 32 GB. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Class 4 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Lexar, Toshiba, Sony, SanDisk, Samsung, Verbatim, PNY. 
</p></li></ul></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">PC/Laptop and SD card reader or convertor Micro SD to Sdcard 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Allen key 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Spanner or socket wrench 5 mm 
</p></li><li id="LI_929C0F12811B4096BB70DA320BD9C6C8" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Protective gloves: 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Microflex</b> 93-260 gloves. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-DB340B14-87E5-4FDB-8108-245D16C84FF1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Protect your eyes from splashing ink: wear safety glasses. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-63708C23-D3ED-4DE1-B712-25A5907F099B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-DBCC6072-817E-44C6-894D-2B19BD5CEA43-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DBCC6072-817E-44C6-894D-2B19BD5CEA43-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_E545FC4D9965419E81D71AAB9ACCD8AA" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to remove</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_B9DB35C90B6749CCA5D79F32429226ED" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the 9 screws. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-AE500B6C-7B66-4A3F-A194-8214BD4E0CA0" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-18DB7C87-1793-4EFC-A8B6-229CAE00030B-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-18DB7C87-1793-4EFC-A8B6-229CAE00030B-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the 3 screws on the top. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the 4 counter parts of the connectors. 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-8D6BAE09-8DE6-4FB3-9FF3-C8F68CF8C43D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-171BE0C3-5520-459A-B0CF-93E09E1127F3-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-171BE0C3-5520-459A-B0CF-93E09E1127F3-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Carefully slide away the cover. 
</p><note id="GUID-8CFDFD9B-C388-4705-BAB4-BD4FE2415CD0" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Keep the connector of the fan connected. 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-46CCA77F-2ECF-4E22-9264-40F3F3E69183" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-895123F2-DAF0-47FB-8233-A4C717E5800A-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-895123F2-DAF0-47FB-8233-A4C717E5800A-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the Micro SD card from the PBA. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-8EFDAA6B-B582-4A37-9072-7E74CDDECC47" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A760F5D6-DA76-4706-ACB3-E63A7C0736A8-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A760F5D6-DA76-4706-ACB3-E63A7C0736A8-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Insert the current or new Micro SD card in a SD card reader or convertor Micro SD to SD card of a PC/Laptop. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Do 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Format the Micro SD card to FAT32. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Create 2 ROOT directories: IMG and LOGS. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The Micro SD card is ready to be used. 
</p></li></ol></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to install and finalize</title><table id="GUID-BDB87D50-9E70-4086-AC9E-FA7970C76B0D" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Install the new or used Micro SD card on the PBA. 
</p><note type="important" id="GUID-5D51E83A-79E7-4A05-863D-1D62687F611F" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> Before installing the cover, coil the wire of the fan around the fan to reduce vibration noise. 
</p></note><p class="- topic/p "> Install the cover and Lamp control PBA (01PBA03) in reverse order. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Reconnect the Service jumper. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Activate SDS 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Do 
<xref keyref="SDS01-1-035" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-D2778EAF-24DE-41F5-8EEE-BCB7BCCBAB96.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>01-1-035 Enable firmware update of curing components [Parameters]</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Enable the firmware update. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-22D79A6A-2191-46FA-BE14-24F47FE4288E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Dis-assembly</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
